*** 229,235 ****
  When using the
  .I "\-\-color"
  option, this version of
! .B ls
  will colorize the file names printed according to the name and type of
  file.  By default, this colorization is by type only, and the codes
  used are ISO 6429 (ANSI) compliant.
--- 229,235 ----
  When using the
  .I "\-\-color"
  option, this version of
! .B gnuls
  will colorize the file names printed according to the name and type of
  file.  By default, this colorization is by type only, and the codes
  used are ISO 6429 (ANSI) compliant.
